            <div type="translation" xml:space="preserve">
            <p> <note>Latin</note> Nero Claudius Drusus Caesar Augustus Germanicus Imperator made roads through the agency of Lucius Pedius Blaesus, proconsul of Crete and Cyrene
</p>
            <p><note>Greek</note> Nero Claudius Drusus Caesar Augustus Germanicus Imperator made roads through the agency of Lucius Pedius Blaesus, proconsul of Crete and Cyrene</p></div>
            
            <div type="commentary">
                <head>Commentary</head>
                <p>1-3. The titulature suggests the first months of Nero’s reign
                    5 (and 13). Pedius Blaesus (<bibl><title>PIR (2)</title>, <citedRange>P212</citedRange></bibl>) 
                    is on record in Tac., Ann. 14.18 and Hist. 1.77.6 as a proconsul prosecuted by Cyrene and condemned for extortion in 59 C.E. but reinstated by Otho.
                </p> <p> Line 15/16: The mileage figure may have been 7 or 8 in the light of the distance from Cyrene</p>
               
                <p> Claudius probably was the first Roman to set up milestones in Kyrenaika </p>
            </div>
